<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>赛琪 |关于人类状况</title><link>https://psyche.co</link><description>Psyche 是 Aeon 的一本数字杂志，通过心理学、哲学和艺术阐明人类状况。</description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 23 Oct 2023 18:18:45 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>为什么当你能在艺术中看到自己时，艺术看起来更美丽</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/5611e3e8-feae-429e-b262-4f0d569b64cb/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;研究表明，当艺术品在某种程度上与个人相关时，人们会觉得艺术品更美观&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——马特·休斯顿&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 23 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/why-art-seems-more-beautiful-when-you-can-see-yourself-in-it?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>一个迷失男孩的歌</title><link>https://psyche.co/films/endearingly-weird-wax-figures-inhabit-a-musical-journey-of-self-discovery?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/0c1dc5e0-4d2b-479e-80c3-acdb164e64b3/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;一场令人愉快、古怪的蜡铸成长冒险，唱诗班男孩失去了声音，但却找到了一个新的社区&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 心灵电影&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/films/endearingly-weird-wax-figures-inhabit-a-musical-journey-of-self-discovery?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;观看 Psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Oct 2023 05:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/films/endearingly-weird-wax-figures-inhabit-a-musical-journey-of-self-discovery?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>敬畏是美德，比勇敢更重要</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/to-fear-well-is-virtuous-and-more-important-than-being-brave?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="俯视一个人在水面上的码头边缘保持平衡的脚趾和脚的特写镜头" src="https://nu.aeon.co/images/1c8697cc-38fe-447b-8b9c-c83f2e4a7c75/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;恐惧不是敌人，而是一种真实而合理的情绪。为了真正支持另一个人的恐惧，让他们发出自己的声音&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——阿米·哈尔滨&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/to-fear-well-is-virtuous-and-more-important-than-being-brave?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 19 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/to-fear-well-is-virtuous-and-more-important-than-being-brave?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如何摆脱气候冷漠</title><link>https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-escape-climate-apathy-and-help-to-avert-catastrophe?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="一对夫妇坐在遮阳伞下的躺椅上，凝视着大海" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/6f7ba40a-0a09-4e83-a7c1-26fb054ed4d5/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;您是否意识到气候紧急情况，但却发现自己把目光移开？以下是如何激发动力并立即采取行动&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——伊丽莎白·克里普斯&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-escape-climate-apathy-and-help-to-avert-catastrophe?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 18 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-escape-climate-apathy-and-help-to-avert-catastrophe?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>当正念遇到资本主义时，它就会迷失方向</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/when-mindfulness-meets-capitalism-it-loses-its-way?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/907d447f-0d1f-4722-94e3-345c3d88c094/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;现代正念商业剥夺了实践的精神意义和实用价值&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——克里斯·惠特利&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/when-mindfulness-meets-capitalism-it-loses-its-way?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 17 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/when-mindfulness-meets-capitalism-it-loses-its-way?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>为了改善你的生活，请考虑改变你的性格</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/to-improve-your-life-consider-changing-your-personality?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="两名身穿粉色和白色兔子服装的妇女在地铁站入口外喝啤酒。其中一个看起来闷闷不乐" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/fa0c2e25-daf3-41bb-9ee1-c0590de812a8/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;新的研究支持这样的观点：有意识地发展某些特征不仅是可能的，而且会带来好处&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——克里斯蒂安·贾勒特&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/to-improve-your-life-consider-changing-your-personality?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 16 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/to-improve-your-life-consider-changing-your-personality?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>生来就温柔</title><link>https://psyche.co/films/a-club-for-dull-men-may-just-inspire-you-to-see-the-unremarkable-anew?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/362c7dc9-c370-4dd3-8f98-dd0d4f7135df/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;沉闷的乐趣 - 如果您喜欢环岛、收集牛奶箱或欣赏饼干，那么总有一个俱乐部适合您&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;- 心灵电影&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/films/a-club-for-dull-men-may-just-inspire-you-to-see-the-unremarkable-anew?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;观看 Psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Oct 2023 10:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/films/a-club-for-dull-men-may-just-inspire-you-to-see-the-unremarkable-anew?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>认识到自由意志是一种幻觉并获得情感上的好处</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/recognise-free-will-is-an-illusion-and-reap-the-emotional-benefits?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="从上方看黄铜和其他材料制成的旋转古董地球仪" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/3a11f587-bd59-43eb-b2a8-afc9a965437f/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;我们所有的选择都是由过去的事件决定的这个想法可能看起来令人沮丧——但它可以在情感上得到解放&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——弗朗西斯·默森&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/recognise-free-will-is-an-illusion-and-reap-the-emotional-benefits?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 12 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/recognise-free-will-is-an-illusion-and-reap-the-emotional-benefits?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>如何少喝酒</title><link>https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-drink-in-a-healthier-way-by-moderating-your-intake?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="平原背景上不平衡酒杯的水彩画" src="https://omicron.aeon.co/images/b8872c3c-7cdb-4465-ac66-2f1f490f3a07/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;你没有上瘾，但你知道自己喝得太多了。学会重新获得控制权并有益于您的身心&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——迈克尔·利维&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-drink-in-a-healthier-way-by-moderating-your-intake?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 11 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/guides/how-to-drink-in-a-healthier-way-by-moderating-your-intake?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item><item><title>为什么很多人认为自己的工作很垃圾？</title><link>https://psyche.co/ideas/why-do-so-many-people-think-they-are-in-a-bullshit-job?utm_source=rss-feed</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="不明确的" src="https://alpha.aeon.co/images/6161745e-20c8-47d3-b9d0-73e046183fb8/original.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;研究人员继续争论某些工作是否本质上是无用的 - 但所有人都同意以这种方式看待你的工作是有害的&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;——莎拉·爱&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://psyche.co/ideas/why-do-so-many-people-think-they-are-in-a-bullshit-job?utm_source=rss-feed"&gt;读《心灵》&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 10 Oct 2023 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://psyche.co/ideas/why-do-so-many-people-think-they-are-in-a-bullshit-job?utm_source=rss-feed</guid></item></channel></rss>